The paper deals with online learning to rank, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). The use of feedback and ranking measures also suggests relevance to the subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). The paper's focus on efficient ranking strategies and regret analysis suggests relevance to the subfield of algorithms and data structures (DS). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, and cs.CL.
